'''The GENTOO_MIRRORS variable contains a space-delimited list of mirror hosts that Portage should use to download source code.'''

A list of [http://www.gentoo.org/main/en/mirrors.xml Gentoo mirrors] is maintained on the Gentoo site.

== Choosing a mirror ==
A good mirror can make Portage download source code faster. Usually, you can choose a mirror that is near you.

A tool called [[mirrorselect|mirrorselect]] is available in the Portage tree, and it can help you choose a fast mirror. You can use the following command to choose a mirror automatically:
{{Cmd|mirrorselect -i -o}}

